        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(channels): shared progress-lane engine — unify per-channel progress streaming",
        "body": "Draft / WIP. Sister to #87072 (Telegram interleaved) and the merged #85200 (Discord commentary). Opening early per @obviyus, who noted a shared approach is better — to align on config naming + sequencing before the channel cutovers.\n\n## Why\n\nTwo channels already implement the *same* concept independently — project an agent's reasoning/tool stream into a live edited progress message:\n- **Telegram** — `interleaved-progress` (#87072): reasoning + tool rows + timestamps + rolling timer + tool-args + 4096 rollover.\n- **Discord** — `streaming.progress.commentary` (#85200, merged, @bryanpearson).\n\nFeishu/MSTeams/lmstudio each have their own `*stream*` modules too. The throttle core (`src/channels/draft-stream-loop.ts`) is already shared; only the *projection* is duplicated. This unifies it.\n\n## What's in this PR so far\n\nA functional, tested, channel-agnostic engine under `src/plugin-sdk/progress-lane/` (no existing channel touched yet):\n- **`transcript.ts`** — pure body math (delta-append + overlap dedup, `computeSpill(maxChars)`, timestamped status lines, rolling-timer render, defensive final-answer strip), hoisted self-contained from #87072.\n- **`controller.ts`** — `createProgressLane({sink, config})`: owns the body, rollover offset, per-stream checkpoints, the timer; wires the generic callbacks (`onReasoning/onCommentary/onTool/onEvent/finalize`) → a sink.\n- **`sink.ts`** — `ProgressLaneSink` (maxChars/render/update/spill) + a **superset `ProgressLaneConfig`** (reasoning/commentary/toolRows/toolArgs/timer) — nothing dropped from either side; Discord's commentary is one toggle.\n- **`controller.test.ts`** — 9 end-to-end cases (gate, reasoning dedup, commentary gate, timestamped tool rows + toolArgs gate, timer stamp, rollover under cap, no-empty-header, final-answer strip). tsgo + oxlint clean, 9/9 green.\n\n## End state — fully unified\n\nEvery channel runs the one engine via a thin sink; no bespoke orchestration survives:\n1. Engine ✓ (this PR).\n2. Channel sinks: **Discord** (next — it already has the edit primitive), MSTeams, Feishu, lmstudio.\n3. **Telegram cutover** — its dispatch delegates to the same `createProgressLane` + a Telegram sink (faithful extraction of its own logic, no behavior change), sequenced **after #87072 merges** to avoid disturbing it.\n\n## Open questions for @obviyus / @bryanpearson\n\n- Canonical config namespace — fold `streaming.preview.interleavedProgress`/`interleavedToolArgs` (TG) + `streaming.progress.commentary` (Discord) into one `streaming.progress.*`? Keep `commentary` as an alias?\n- Sink contract: neutral body string (current) vs structured segments for card channels (Teams/Feishu) — leaning add-segments-when-cards-land.\n- Sequencing: land engine + new-channel sinks first, Telegram cutover after #87072 merges?\n\nRefs: #87072, #85200, #85164.",
